Dave?s one of those, you see, what he would like to call Stoics, determined in the face of his haunts, drifting on the edge of his vision day to day, to be unruled by his own unruly impulses. Oh, make no mistake, he had a great love once, a proper feminine love into the likes of which we men are meant to walk ourselves; nor would he be loathe, by any means, given reasonably propitious material circumstances, to do it again, given due consideration from as detached a third-party perspective as possible, given, above all, patience, and time to sort everything left, particularly with regard to the fallout of the said affair, his great love, which still impinges on him in a very real, material manner, for one hour, every morning.